                <h2 class="section-title">Our Business Model</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">
                    Our go-to-market strategy is to test multiple revenue models, starting with two distinct experiments: user subscriptions and strategic B2B partnerships. Our hypothesis is that while subscriptions will build our foundational user base, partnerships will unlock high-margin revenue-sharing opportunities with major distribution partners. The chart below is illustrative of a potential long-term revenue mix.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800">Primary Revenue Streams</h3>
                        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
                           <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-sky-500 text-xl mr-3">▶</span><div><h4 class="font-semibold">Subscription Access</h4><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Tiered plans for individuals and enterprises.</p></div></li>
                           <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-sky-500 text-xl mr-3">▶</span><div><h4 class="font-semibold">Usage-Based Fees</h4><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Per-query charges for specialized consultations.</p></div></li>
                           <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-sky-500 text-xl mr-3">▶</span><div><h4 class="font-semibold">API Access</h4><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Licensing our agents to third-party platforms.</p></div></li>
                           <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-sky-500 text-xl mr-3">▶</span><div><h4 class="font-semibold">Platform Partnerships</h4><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Revenue sharing with strategic partners like Google.</p></div></li>
